				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\sim40\%$\end{document} of background emissions in a direction of very low cosmic background intensity originate from the He focusing cone and not the local hot bubble surrounding the heliosphere (Galeazzi et¬†al. 2014; Snowden et¬†al. 2014, 2015; Uprety et¬†al. 2016; Liu et¬†al. 2017). Fig.¬†34
