There are a number of caveats. First, even with a large number of counts, the FOV may not be broad enough to capture the bulk of the magnetosheath emission profile, in which case no algorithm will produce a reasonable measure. The vignetting function should be flat for roughly twice the width of the magnetosheath or else the shape of the peak and the shape of the vignetting function become confused. On the Earthward side, the profile should extend to at least the minimum between the cusps and the magnetosheath; on the Sunward side, the profile should extend at least to the bow shock, if one is interested only in the location of the magnetopause, and ‚àº10‚àò\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
